Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The burnt bodies of two unidentified people were found in Lavender Hill, Cape Town on Saturday. Western Cape police spokesperson Andre Traut says the circumstances of the deaths are being investigated. WATCH: Five-year-old boy shot dead in Lavender Hill "According to an eye witness account, a group of approximately 30 people were seen with four unidentified men. Two were set alight and two managed to escape." READ: Rashied Staggie's daughter lashes out at media Traut says the motive is unknown. Police also say they are searching for the two victims who escaped. Watch the full interview with Western Cape police spokesperson Andre Traut above.